result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Matthew C. Fell

records.descr: Records of prosec. are converted data. See file.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Matthew C. Fell in court.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court calls  @ 11:30 am  Cases called 15CF71 and 15CM104.  State moves to dismiss 15CM104 and read in for restitution.  15CF71 amend ct 1 to criminal tresspass and plea to other counts .  Balance of plea agreement stated on record.  Court reviews right to an atty.  Def wishes to proceed without cousel.  Court will proceed.  Victim rights have been complied with.  15CM104 Court will dismiss and read in for restitution $976.00.  15CF71 Ct 1 amended to Criminal Trespass. Court reviews elements of charges.   Ct 1 Guilty to amend.  Ct 2 Guilty plea.  Ct 3  Guilty plea.  Plea questionnaire form reviewed.  Constitutional rights reviewed.  Def waives rights.  Court reviews penalties.  Court finds def understands charges, penalties and rights.  Pleas accepted, found guilty.  Factual basis in complaint.  State presents sentencing arguments.  Nothing by def.  Court will accept plea agreement.  Ct 1 Sentence withheld 2 yrs probation.  Alcohol and drug counseling and follow through  Restitution $4667.82 and $976.00  Cost.  Sentence to be the same on Ct 2 & 3 Concurrent.   Court orders $200.00 DNA surcharge on each count.  DNA sample ordered.  Credit 1 day if revoked.    If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.   Post conviction rights
